						               													<description>Somewhere in a 3rd world country, you are a laborer who tries to survive daily without enough state welfare benefits. When a pandemic occurs, you have to decide to risk your life by working outside or staying safe at home without cash to spend.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In 3rd world labour, there are construction sites that players have to build them up. When the 4th building was completed, the richest player will be a winner. Yes, in the 3rd world country the richest man always wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, players have to decide to take action between &amp;quot;Go to work outside&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;Stay safe at home&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Go to work outside&amp;quot; &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Pick a construction site to work&amp;#10;     Place the corresponding color of blocks on the construction site.&amp;#10;     If the block is placed on a star symbol, take a bonus event card.&amp;#10;     Take income equal to the number of blocks placed and spend the expense.&amp;#10;     If there are other players on the same site, the player has to take a sickness card. When there are more than 2 sickness cards, reveal the rightmost card and take effect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Stay safe at home&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Roll the dice and spend the expense.&amp;#10;     Discard all the sickness cards.&amp;#10;     Spend the money to buy the new skill card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player can take the free action to buy the lotto, pay their debt, and take more loans anytime in their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For each building that was completed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The player who finished that building gets 3 coins.&amp;#10;     all players have to pay the interest according to their debt card.&amp;#10;     The lotto prize was announced.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And the winner is the richest player when the 4th building was completed!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Why ?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Because the richest man can survive by buying the better service that their government can't provide to citizens by themself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
